caption: This spot never fails to impress. They serve awesome food for convenient pricing, there are no long waits even when they are packed.
I always come by getting some food in this spot. I love the swift customer service and well cooked dishes. 5 stars from me.
I love this place!, Best food ever and great prices. Give this place a try it is wonderful! Owned and ran by the nicest people ever! Thank you East Wave Asian Fusion!
The best nacos ever
Can you say heaven
Good food, community styled dining. Fresh ingredients, great variety and friendly staff.

Vegan Friendly Review: I have gone to lunch at East Wave Asian Fusion several times with co-workers and solo. I have gotten the Garlic Tofu and Broccoli w/brown rice every time and it has been consistently flavorful and a ton of food for $7 and some change. The employees are always upbeat and work efficiently even when Georgia State is in session when the lunch crowd becomes hectic. East Wave Asian is a wonderful choice in downtown Atlanta as a lovely Asian fusion choice!

Amazingly delicious food at East Wave Asian Fusion!  Came here for lunch with a girlfriend after having this place on my waitlist for awhile. Everything was flavorful, yummy, and fresh!  Some favorites are the garlic noodles, wasabi noodles, deep fried salmon roll, BBQ oysters, ahi-tuna special, and the octopus appetizer.  Food, service and cleanliness all on point without being overbearing. Perfect for lunches with family and friends, even date nights!  Affordable food for what you get specially for the area! Definitely give this place a visit!

Absolutely love this place and will certainly return here when I'm back in Georgia! The family that runs it is completely delightful! The food is phenomenal and the atmosphere is fun and peaceful!! We enjoyed the bulgoghi beef, the baohs, the pot stickers and the incredible cheese burger egg rolls!! Whether you live here or you're here on travel make this a destination for lunch or an early dinner!

Wow another home run for Atlanta. I'd say mom and pop but this is a son owned mom and sisters run amazing eatery. Can't say enough good about this place. Definitely give the cheese burger egg rolls a try, as well as baohs, bulgoghi beef and of course the pot stickers. Everything is made in house by mom. Being from Texas momma's cooking is always a winner. Amazing customer service. The place gets busy so be patient it's worth the wait.

I used to work a block away from this location and visited serveral times. I ordered the honey chicken and fried rice (absolutely loved how crispy the chicken was, although the sauce was a little too sweet) and the rice wasn't dry at all. They weren't burnt to the point where I couldn't even eat them, but I definitely could taste the difference versus them not being burnt
The lettuce wraps are cheap enough to try them all in one sitting. OMG the flavors are off the chart. I highly recommend this place for a quick bite.
Loved their chicken fried rice, dumplings and crab rangoons.

Nice location for tasty asian food. Do yourself a favor and try this place. Definitely worth a return visit. Bring your appetite because portions are generous. Feels like a place in Los Angeles I liked.
Yum!  We love coming here! Service is usually pretty good/quick. Food quality is always excellent!
Food is usually hot and fresh,  but they have a high turnover rate, maybe because they employ college students and they graduate and move on.

I regularly eat here between classes, ordering the (pictured) crispy honey chicken with broccoli, with a side of fried rice. In short, it's good stuff. I've had several other dishes as well and they know what they're doing in bringing authentic Asian cuisine. However, it's a bit overpriced. Overall, though, good place. GSU students, go in on Tuesdays for a discount!

East Wave is alright. Good for if you're hungry and have money to spare for a food budget. As a college student, this place is kinda overpriced depending on what you get. I had gotten the lettuce wraps when I was here, but they weren't worth paying over $10 to bite into small wraps that I could have made at home. I hope they adjust their prices to their cuisine, especially considering that Dua is right up the road. If you want modern cuisine and to try something new, this could be a good spot, but keep in mind your wallet when eating here.
Nice place
I love this place!! The best ever!!
Okay
Brilliant food and extremely quick. If you want quick, amazingly hygienic and great asian food - this is the place to go. Special shout out to the bubble tea!!

Used to be 5 stars for me but today was a turning point. I used to frequent this place because the food was great and the restaurant was beautiful. I absolutely loved the boba teas. But today I went and ordered my regular meal and they stopped serving boba. They also stopped having the option to omit peas and carrots from the rice (I am allergic to peas) in favor of cooking it bulk and sending it out as quickly as possible. I probably won’t be coming back as a customer but I still do believe their food is good and the atmosphere is very nice so I’ll be sure to show my friends from college this place.
I Love dining here! The food and service are great.
I can’t keep up with kids these days, but this place was great! I need to go buy sunglasses now.
I always come here for the udon. What would  make it better is if they sold read like they did before.

I love the boba tea here, they discontinued it for a while which made me go to boba mocha, which make horribly bad milk teas but I'm glad they r back with these. The boba seeds are well soaked and chewy, not excessively sweet. I also like fried egg roll here
A great place if you're looking for great quality fusion.
great
The baos are homemade and very scrumptious. Friendly staff, plenty of seating, clean, outlets to hook up a laptop.

The Chipotle chicken tastes delicious. I ordered a banh mi sandwich meal with Chipotle chicken, cost about $9.25. the sweet plantains tasted good too. It is definitely a fast casual place. Would recommend for employees in the area.
good
Yummy, slightly pricey Asian fusion food. It's always busy at lunch time, and the small ordering area will be packed, so get there BEFORE noon - more like 11:15 or 11:30 am!
Confusing menu for first timers. The price is a bit high, but the portions are large. Expect to be here for a while if you're not a fast eater.
The service was nice. It's a little pricey, and the menu can be a little confusing with the combos. The food was good and had large portions. The restaurant is rather large and has nice seatings.
Great customer service
Took 15min for some hard cooked fries that taste more like pure honey than teriyaki

Service was quick and the food is really good, I only have a couple of problems though. First, the menu on their website doesn't have any prices so I had to call and see what everything would cost as I was ordering over the phone, which I'm not a big fan of.  Second, they got part of my order wrong. I wanted the mama egg rolls, but they gave me cheeseburger egg rolls instead. They weren't bad, just not what I ordered. I'll probably come back because the food is good and this is one of the few places I have found that has Bahn Mi.
Ok spot, my salad seem bigger than my plate. Not good!
I love their bubble tea!
Slipped in the door at closing unknowingly and these guys were sooo accomodating!! The best cheeseburger egg rolls! Great Friday treat!!
I always go there if I am in the area and craving milk teas with tapioca bubble. Not too sweet and smooth tasting teas.

I had the crab Rangoons and the kale salad BOTH BANNGINNN. Reasonably priced and great portions. The only reason I didn't give it 5 starts is becuase, they close at 4 and I need to try more food options. Lol.
Really good beef broccoli stir fry!
First fast food Asian food I've seen
Closed earlier 630pm than stated (730pm) , rude waitress. Unacceptable!!
Great shrimp tacos
Super friendly staff, upbeat environment, and overpriced food thats still pretty good
Good lunch spot in Fairlie Poplar area
Usually busy. Drinks are pretty good. Hours are -_-
Nice and friendly
Food is great! Price is ridiculous!
I love the bubble tea smoothies!
Great hangout spot for students.
Dope

I've gone there twice already. First time it was an extremely long wait for my food. I went today and there hardly any customers still had a long wait and they got my order wrong. Will definitely not go again.
Reasonable price and good tasting food. Not your normal stuff. I would suggest trying it. Get something you don't normally eat.

I've only had one of the entrees there (crispy honey chicken I think), but honestly it's really good. I just usually go there for the tea and I just keep coming back. The staff is really great, and it's always kept clean. Would recommend definitely.

Love this place! I come here all the time and have never been disappointed. Their Samosas are delicious! They also have so many flavors of Fruit Tea and Bubble Tea! If you’re having trouble deciding what to order, the staff is super friendly and ready to help you.
Great food..l love the Bao Asain Taco like sandwich... great  outside sitting under trees great  for people watching or just relaxing. .

I went for "Thirsty Thursday" and tried a fruit tea and it was great! it was a lemon green tea with strawberry bits & boba (if that's how you spell it). The only gripe I had this go around was the wait time. I placed my order before a lot of others who came in yet their orders were done ahead of mine because the drink makers grabbed the cups at random instead of a first come first serve basis. Personally, I think this place would benefit greatly from a uniform system that works on a first come first serve basis prioritizing call-ins. but again, you can't beat the ambience & the employees seem happy to be there & it shows in the service.
Great food, even better music
LOTS of fantastic food for the price, great atmosphere and super friendly management.

After hearing my friend's rave review of East Wave she convinced me to make a visit with her. We had a great experience. The restaurant is modern, bright and feels really clean. The staff was kind and patient as we read over the new menu and they made suggestions, too! My friend and I shared jasmine green milk tea, pork buns & chicken dumplings. Everything was delicious! A neon photo mural on the wall caught my eye, so I asked Alex, who turned out to be the manager/ co-owner. He told me it's of some old Korean & Chinese buildings. All three of us then talked about our mutual love of food and culture for a while. We were able to get our paws on a few new versions of their teas. The lychee, matcha, Thai tea, taro, and green apple are just a few of their new creations. Our favorites were the green apple and the lychee flavors, which were lightly sweet and very refreshing. Final statement: We will be back & referring.
Everyone I know has said great things about this place and I am glad I finally went. There is something for everyone! Great food the whole family enjoyed. I can't wait to go back!
The food was great. I love the atmosphere, the design  of the place and everyone  works  as a team , I do see myself  going back to East wave Asian Fusion.

My favorite restaurant didnt have its usual Tues off menu item so i walked into East Wave.  (FYI, entrance is really on Broad Street.) It was excellent!  I'm so glad I went in.  I got the Chipotle & Soy Grilled Pork Bun.  It's an ihouse made Bun, very large, ample meat, topped with a carrot/cabbage slaw (typical vietnamese and/or Korean i think.) It was vreally good.  Three of them for $7.50, and more than enough for a meal.   Its now my other favorite restaurant on Broad Street.  You dont come to a place like this for fried rice or tossed noodles.  You come and order the unusual, and they definitely have it.
This place was really gross and I found a hair in my food. Waste of money, I had the chow fun noodles and vegetable spring roll. The spring roll wasn't terrible but those "noodles" were gross.
Great food and sleek design. They have the most delicious crispy chicken wings, bubble tea, lobster rolls and so much more. I will definitely be back
